Wanted: Editions of Diplomacy and Information About Them

I'm putting together a chronology and gallery of various editions of
Diplomacy that have been put out.  I've identified around 20 different
editions as well as several editions of Diplomacy variant games, and
there are probably some that I don't know about.  Below is a list of
editions I know about:

UNITED STATES 
  Allan Calhamer: 1958
  Games Research Inc.: 1961, 1971
  Avalon Hill Game Co.: 1976, 1982, 1992 (Deluxe edition)
  New Avalon Hill Game Co. (Hasbro): 1999 (copyright 1999, released 2000)
UNITED KINGDOM
  Intellectual Diversions: several editions
  Gibson's Games: Two different editions, both copyright 1989
CANADA
  Waddington's House of Games: one edition has rules copyright 1974 and
      a map copyright 1971, a different edition has a gameboard with a
      gold-colored backing.
  Waddington Sanders: 1986
FRANCE 
  Parker: 1978
  Descartes Editeur: 
AUSTRALIA
  Jedko:
NETHERLANDS
  Jumbo:
GERMANY
  Parker: 1977
DIPLOMACY VARIANTS (ALL FROM UNITED STATES)
  Colonial Diplomacy: 1994
  Machiavelli - Battleline Games: 1977
  Machiavelli - Avalon Hill: 1980, 1983, 1995
  (Rumors regarding Hundred, Classical, Ard-Ri)

I would be interested in any information anyone has about editions
that are not on the above list.  If you know of an edition that is
not listed above, please let me know.  

Although I have been slowly gathering information about the editions
listed above, in several cases my information is not complete,
particularly for those editions that were published outside of the 
United States.  If you have an edition of Diplomacy from outside of
the U.S. and would be willing to provide me with some information,
please drop me an email.

Lastly, there are several non-U.S. editions that I would be interested
in obtaining.  If you have an edition of Diplomacy from outside the U.S.
and would be willing to consider selling or trading it, please let me
know.

Thanks very much.  I hope to have the chronology and gallery up on the
web in one of the Fall issues of the Pouch Zine.

- Simon


