Subject: DipPouch article feedback
Errors-To: manus@devel.diplom.org
Status: OR

It seems to me that an alternative way of fixing the paradox problem would be to make a fundamental alteration to the rules and say that if the total force trying to move in to a region is greater than the total force occupying that region then the unit occupying the region is forced to retreat. This is surely nearer the real-life situation, in that someone sitting in the middle of the battlefield is going to get rather shot up. In the example given, this would result in F(ENG) being forced to retreat, the convoy being broken and everything else bouncing. I can't think of any obvious ways in which it would result in new inconsistencies, provided it is applied uniformly and not just when paradoxes occur.
If I've missed something obvious, then sorry for wasting your time; otherwise, is this change too fundamental or what are your opinions on it?

Yours,

Peter Taylor

